The murder case against Marthinus Pelser was once agained postponed in the Krugersdorp Magistrates&#8217; Court on Friday. This time, the case was postponed due to the fact that the state did not have the docket in court, Krugersdorp News reported. READ MORE: Pelser defence strategy becoming clearer Pelser s defense, Advocate van Rensburg, asked that the case be postponed until December 1. Pelser appeared via audiovisual remand (AVR) today. He stands accused of having murdered his six-month-old baby boy in May this year. &#8211; Caxton News Service